The Minister of Federal Capital Territory, FCT, Mohammed Musa Bello has recovered from COVID-19 disease after testing positive for the virus on December 31, 2021. Bello who confirmed his current status on Monday via a post on his official Facebook page said he is now fit to resume office duty. He lauded the FCTA Medical team for their commitment and dedication to duty while attending to COVID-19 patients across the territory. The Minister called on residents of the nation’s capital to ensure that they are vaccinated against the disease, stressing that COVID-19 is very much around. He said, “Best regards to all. Pleased to report that after taking my prescribed course of COVID-19 medication, I feel very well and great. The doctors have confirmed that I’m now free of the virus and it’s OK for me to resume all official activities. “I wish to convey my sincere appreciation to all those who showed great concern for my health status, through various channels of communication. “I also wish to commend the FCTA Medical team for their commitment and dedication to duty. All COVID-19 patients in the FCT are truly thankful to you. “Let me use this opportunity to further reiterate that COVID-19 is very much around. I, therefore, once more, appeal to residents to get themselves vaccinated. Doing so could save their lives”.